text: Mycale hentscheli is a marine sponge, which is known to be a rich source of bioactive small molecules. These natural products originate from the sponge's microbiota. Examples of these molecules include the potent cytotoxic polyketides: pateamine, peloruside, and mycalamide. ==References== ==External links== * Anti-cancer sponge:the race is on for aquaculture supply Category:Poecilosclerida
title: Mycale hentscheli
